mulberry (4.2.0a1) unstable; urgency=medium

  IMPORTANT: Upgrading from older builds

  This is the first version with significant development activity in
  over a decade. Users upgrading from older builds should be aware of
  the following:

  * 64-bit Native Build
    - This is a native 64-bit build (x86_64)
    - Offline mail cache files from 32-bit builds may be corrupted due
      to type size changes; delete and re-sync if you encounter issues
    - If you experience preferences corruption, remove
      ~/.mulberry/preferences.mbp and reconfigure

  * OpenSSL 3.x
    - Mulberry now loads system OpenSSL dynamically (1.1 through 3.x)
    - The bundled OpenSSL 0.9.8m has been removed

  * Desktop Integration
    - Mulberry now appears in application menus under Network > Email
    - Registered as handler for mailto: and webcal: URLs
    - Attachments and links open via xdg-open when no mailcap/helpers
      mapping exists

  * Known Limitations
    - Compose key input limited to ISO 8859-1 characters (JX toolkit)
    - No OAuth2 authentication support
    - Subject prefix stripping has no preferences UI yet (editable in
      preferences file directly)

  For the full list of changes, see CHANGELOG.md or
  /usr/share/doc/mulberry/changelog.gz

 -- yitzhaq <github@anonmail.uk>  Fri, 25 Apr 2026 03:00:00 +0200
